title: Modify OSLMP_API_ABI declaration
message:
Modify OSLMP_API_ABI declaration

The __NDK_FPABI__ definition has been removed from the latest NDK package.
It is not required anymore because it was introduced to support armeabi-v7a-hard
psuedo ABI which has already been deprecated.

title: Tweak audio sink buffer size and count to avoid audio glitch
message:
Tweak audio sink buffer size and count to avoid audio glitch

Audio glitches still can be occurs especially on heavy CPU load.
This cannot be avoided because the cause is buffer underrun occurs in
the Android audio framework (AudioTrack).

When AudioTrack is running in PULL (NON BLOCKING) mode, its destination
buffer is used as double-buffing and the buffer is not so large
(about 2.3k samples = 24 ms on Nexus 5x). On heavy CPU load which causes
more than half-buffer size duration delay, audio glitch happens.

MediaPlayer and AudioTrack (BLOCKING mode) are more tolerant, because
it allows more large size buffering.
